<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-29T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/401</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-29T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5511. Your telegram September 17.<note n="1" xml:id="d90fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> Except for certain quantity of food grains which
                                were allowed to go to Sweden and Norway as result of agreements made
                                with Governments those countries, whereby a double quantity of food
                                grains were released for Belgian Relief, and some few other special
                                isolated cases of shipments to Norway, nothing is going to
                                Scandinavian countries.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>